Definition: an autonomous republic in southwestern Russia in the northern Caucasus Mountains bordering on Georgia
Example: declared independence from the USSR in 1991 but Russian troops invaded and continue to prosecute a relentless military campaign in the largely Muslim republic
Synonyms: Chechenia, Chechen_Republic, geographical_area, i, Russia, p, an, autonomous, republic, in, southwestern, the, northern, Caucasus, Mountains, bordering, on, Georgia, declared, independence, from, USSR, but, Russian, troops, invaded, and, continue, to, prosecute, a, relentless, military, campaign, largely, Muslim
Category: noun.location
